    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, newbie here.</p>\n<p>I have a rather simple question: How to turn a goal of the form b \\ge a to a goal of the form a \\le b?</p>\n<p>I've seen that b \\ge a is an abbreviation for a \\le b, so I thought the following would work (from Glimpse of Lean):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extraction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">‚Ñï</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">‚Ñï</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚àÄ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">id_le_extraction'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extraction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚àÄ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hyp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">zero_le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">succ_le_of_lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hyp</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lt_add_one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extraction_ge</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extraction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚àÄ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚àÉ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hyp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">le_max_right</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">id_le_extraction'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hyp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, before even being able to finish the proof, I got an error.<br>\nEven more confusingly, it says</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">'</span><span class=\"k\">calc</span><span class=\"bp\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expression</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">has</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â§</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n<span class=\"n\">but</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">N'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And I have no clue why the <code>max N N' ‚â• N' : Prop</code> is \"expected\".</p>\n<p>Any help?</p>",
        "id": 542782237,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759421636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>PS: I know that I can do the calc the \"other way around\" to comply with the inequality in the goal, but I still want to know how to flip the inequality and why it's giving me that error message.</p>",
        "id": 542782505,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759421724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Update: I figured it out, and turns out I'm just terrible at reading... How do I delete an entire topic? lol...</p>",
        "id": 542782733,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759421807
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"971939\">@Labyrinth</span> btw the idiomatic answer is that <code>\\ge</code> is not supported and you should use <code>\\le</code> everywhere.</p>",
        "id": 542783342,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422002
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span> Not supported? By what? Lean 4 Web seems to understand it fine</p>",
        "id": 542783515,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422052
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it means \"just don't use it at all\"</p>",
        "id": 542783628,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422089
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>not supported by the wealth of theorems that are in mathlib</p>",
        "id": 542783691,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422109
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Kenny, that's not really accurate. Just because our style guidelines say \"prefer ‚â§ to ‚â•\" doesn't mean the latter is \"not supported\" or you \"shouldn't use it\".</p>",
        "id": 542783858,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422162
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact, <code>‚àÉ n ‚â• N</code> is <em>exactly</em> one of the cases that we use <em>throughout Mathlib</em>.</p>",
        "id": 542783952,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422187
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span> Is it that bad? I can only believe you - I haven't done much in Lean yet to contradict anyone, but shouldn't defining it as an abbreviation for <code>le</code> work just fine?</p>",
        "id": 542784108,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422237
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact, <code>a ‚â• b</code> is already an abbreviation for <code>b ‚â§ a</code>, so you should be able to use them (almost) interchangeably everywhere.</p>",
        "id": 542784290,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>my answer to that would be, <code>abbrev</code> isn't as strong as I would like it to be, it doesn't actually behave as abbreviation everywhere, Lean still actually treats them as different objects</p>",
        "id": 542784368,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would like to see <code>notation</code> everywhere basically</p>",
        "id": 542784483,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422336
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What's the difference between <code>abbrev</code> and <code>notation</code>?</p>",
        "id": 542784563,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422361
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sure, but it's <em>almost</em> the same, and there's no need to confuse new users by saying they should never write <code>‚â•</code>.</p>",
        "id": 542784586,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422367
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, working with <code>a ‚â• b</code> is totally fine but mathlib prefers the spelling <code>b ‚â§ a</code>. In other words, you can use all of mathlib's API just as well with <code>‚â•</code> with maybe <code>ge_iff_le</code> sometimes but this is simply not done in mathlib</p>",
        "id": 542784601,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1759422371
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To answer one of the original question, you can do this to explicitly flip the inequality </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ge_iff_le</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 542784655,
        "sender_full_name": "Weiyi Wang",
        "timestamp": 1759422389
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>notation</code> is <em>syntactically</em> equal to the original, while <code>abbrev</code> is <em>reducibly definitionally equal</em> to the original.</p>",
        "id": 542784766,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there any situation in which the difference matters?</p>",
        "id": 542784843,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422449
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, when you have an <code>abbrev</code>, you will still see the name (or the notation) of the <code>abbrev</code> and not of the underlying definition. With syntax, writing it either way has literally no noticeable difference</p>",
        "id": 542785147,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1759422534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This sometimes matters for e.g. <code>rw</code> because <code>rw</code> works more on a basis of \"syntactical\" equality</p>",
        "id": 542785285,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1759422568
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>Well, when you have an¬†<code>abbrev</code>, you will still see the name (or the notation) of the¬†<code>abbrev</code>¬†and not of the underlying definition. With syntax, writing it either way has literally no noticeable difference</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So, it affects the \"goal view\" or whatever it's called(?)</p>",
        "id": 542785518,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes, but it's a small-ish difference which I would ignore while you're still learning. Basically, <code>notation</code> is for providing <em>notation</em> (e.g., <code>M ‚Üí* N</code> for <code>MonoidHom M N</code>) whereas <code>abbrev</code> is for defining two things which are the same under the hood, but you like to have a different name for it, e.g., <code>StrongDual ùïú E</code> is an abbreviation for <code>E ‚ÜíL[ùïú] ùïú</code> (which itself is notation for <code>ContinuousLinearMap (RingHom.id ùïú) E E</code>).</p>",
        "id": 542785584,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422652
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Understood. Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 542785912,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759422742
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"971939\">Labyrinth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Flipping.20an.20inequality/near/542784843\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is there any situation in which the difference matters?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>yes, <code>abbrev</code> creates a new object that Lean unfolds most of the time, and <code>notation</code> means that it's just a shorthand and to Lean they are always the same object</p>",
        "id": 542785938,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422749
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think I would still like to insist on the point that mathlib \"basically always\" prefers &lt;= over &gt;=</p>",
        "id": 542786327,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759422857
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Kenny, if <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"971939\">Labyrinth</span> were writing a PR, then this would be a relevant comment, but for a new user not trying to contribute to Mathlib at the moment, it's just noise. But sure, you're correct that Mathlib almost always prefers <code>‚â§</code>.</p>",
        "id": 542786656,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759422949
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's relevant if they are trying to use theorems in lean / mathlib and not finding the theorems they want for &gt;= and only finding the &lt;= theorems</p>",
        "id": 542786814,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759423000
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>they still basically have to use <code>ge_iff_le</code> to turn every &gt;= into &lt;=</p>",
        "id": 542786866,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759423014
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, for finding lemmas it's helpful to know. I take back what I said about your \"basically always\" comment, as I was conflating it with your earlier comment that <code>‚â•</code> is \"not supported\" or \"shoudn't be used\".</p>",
        "id": 542787982,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1759423406
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Unrelated side note: I love Lean (&lt;insert image of original \"I Love Lean!!!\" meme but edited to have Lean 4 on top of the drink&gt;). I was trying to use Rocq not long ago, and I could not find proper documentation or tutorials for beginners. The entry barrier was just too strong and academic. Lean 4 has been really easy to pick up, and in just an hour or two I got more progress than in several hours of trying to make Rocq work</p>",
        "id": 542791412,
        "sender_full_name": "Labyrinth",
        "timestamp": 1759424592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I had a pre-edit comment here about thinking that local hypotheses of <code>&gt;</code> or <code>\\ge</code> were useful for <code>grw</code>, but I think I've talked myself out of it. It seems like <code>‚Üê</code> suffices to manipulate either side of an inequality in either a hypothesis or goal, even if all goals in sight are <code>&lt;</code> or <code>\\le</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">grw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- now k : a &lt; c</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">grw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üê</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- now k : c &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">‚Ñù</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">grw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- now goal is c &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> 